Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja A staff members of the Nigerian Communications Commission, Nuhu Gabdo, his wife, four children, niece and driver all died in a road accident on Saturday. According to the NCC in a statement on Sunday, the victims died on Saturday along Nasarawa-Abuja Expressway. Spokesperson for the commission, Ikechukwu Adinde, said, “Gabdo died alongside his wife, four children, his niece and driver in an accident that occured on Saturday, January 9, 2021 along Nasarawa-Abuja Expressway.” He said the deceased and his family were returning from their country home, Serti in Gashaka Local Government Area of Taraba State. Until his death, Gabdo was a Principal Manager in the Human Capital and Administration Department of the commission. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com  